comment:
* A subclass of Factory that uses LocaleKeys.  If 'visible' the
     * factory reports its IDs.
     * @hide Only a subset of ICU is exposed in Android

methods.name: public Object create(Key key, ICUService service)
methods.comment:
* Implement superclass abstract method.  This checks the currentID of
         * the key against the supported IDs, and passes the canonicalLocale and
         * kind off to handleCreate (which subclasses must implement).

methods.name: public String getDisplayName(String id, ULocale locale)
methods.comment: * Return a localized name for the locale represented by id.

methods.name: protected Object handleCreate(ULocale loc, int kind, ICUService service)
methods.comment:
* Utility method used by create(Key, ICUService).  Subclasses can
         * implement this instead of create.

methods.name: protected boolean isSupportedID(String id)
methods.comment:
* Return true if this id is one the factory supports (visible or
         * otherwise).

methods.name: protected Set<String> getSupportedIDs()
methods.comment:
* Return the set of ids that this factory supports (visible or
         * otherwise).  This can be called often and might need to be
         * cached if it is expensive to create.

methodNames: public Object create(Key key, ICUService service)
public String getDisplayName(String id, ULocale locale)
protected Object handleCreate(ULocale loc, int kind, ICUService service)
